# Logic to Move Zeroes to the End

**Given Array**

```text
[1,2,0,4,5,0,6,7]
```

**Expected Array**

```text
[1,2,4,5,6,7,0,0]
```

## Brute Force

Run a loop from index `0` to the end of the array.

If a `0` is found, shift all the elements after that zero by one position to the left and place `0` at the last index.

After placing the zero at the end, decrease the last index (`last--`) because that zero is already at its correct position.

Repeat this process until the entire array is traversed.

**Time Complexity:** `O(n²)`

**Space Complexity:** `O(1)`

---

## Optimal Approach

Traverse the array and find the first zero.

```java
int j = -1;
```

If a zero is found, store its index in `j` and break the loop.

If `j == -1`, it means there is no zero in the array, so no changes are required.

Now start another loop from `j + 1` to the end of the array.

If the current element is not zero, swap it with `arr[j]` and increment `j`.

If the current element is zero, do nothing and continue the loop.

By the end of the traversal, all the non-zero elements will be in their correct order and all the zeroes will automatically be moved to the end.

**Time Complexity:** `O(n + n) = O(2n) = O(n)`

**Space Complexity:** `O(1)`
